{
  "texts": [
    "This trend is expected to continue to grow in the next few years.",
    "While only 3% of all feed produced is for pets, 50% of the insect industry is engaged in producing for this sector (van Huis, 2022).",
    "In vitro assays displayed that fraction containing BSF larvae protein significantly inhibited the growth of Clostridium perfringens, which is for 28% of the cases responsible for diarrhoea in dogs (Dong et al., 2021).",
    "However, Bosch and Swanson (2021) caution that health-promoting effects of insect products need to be studied more as well as the long-term impact of insects as food on the nutritional status of dogs and cats.",
    "Concerning indispensable amino acids, the limiting ones with BSF methionine and threonine for dogs and the first methionine for cats (Bosch et al., 2019)."
